    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-08-31T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-08-31T23:00:00-05:00" n="465"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7596: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-09-01T12:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 1, 1926—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received September 1—5:51 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>362. My 357, August 27, 3 p.m.</p>
                <p>1. Following from American consul general, Hankoitem: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“August 31, 10 a.m. Wu Pei-fu has suffered serious setback at the hands
                            of the Southerners and has fallen back early this morning. Southern
                            troops now very near Wuchang. Admiral Hough<note n="20"
                                xml:id="d465fn20">Rear Admiral Henry H. Hough, U. S. N., commander
                                of the Yangtze Patrol.</note> returning today via commercial
                            transport. <hi rend="italic">Isabel</hi> in Shanghai for overhauling;
                                <hi rend="italic">Polos</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Portage</hi> [<hi
                                rend="italic">Pigeon?</hi>] now here. Suggest that destroyers be
                            sent here at once as a precautionary measure since there is some danger
                            of looting from the retreating forces. Local American community requests
                            this measure of security.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>2. I concur in suggestion regarding despatch of destroyers to Hankow and have so
                    informed commander in chief, United States Asiatic Fleet, repeating to him
                    Lockhart’s telegram aforementioned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
